comments: ["Overall impressions is that at this stage, the apps not worth the time. The biggest issue is that there are absolutely nobody on here. Even in a major Metroplex there is no one on here outside of the occasional working girl. I can log in at any point and there be nothing. No one is interested in this app and quite frankly it's but one of many trying to prey on men trying to get their rocks off.", "Bots, bots, bots. Two matches one initially England and then after the message usa, second also England and after first message norther Ireland. Also keep begging you to go to Telegram, I don't even know what that is but it was clearly a scam/bot account. Terrible app and after a couple days no matches within 200 miles. Savage and yeah don't bother with this thing.", "Not bad at all, only issue is... If your looking for people in your area. Your not gonna come across to many people... I had to set the setting for distance to 200 miles away and there obviously more people to see, that are closer but then your limited on how many people you can like. Then have to wait so many hours to be able to react again, but then the app tells you there isnt anymore profiles to see and to adjust your settings. That's the only thing I dont really like about it.", "Downloaded this app because I was like 'oh a new app, wonder what's it about' then it basically told me in order to continue I need to verify my account which is fine, but a hour goes by of me not using it, I get a like, and it tells me my verification failed and I got kicked out the system and I couldn't recreate a account and I even tried to uninstall and redownload it, nothing. I can't use my number or a email address", "Need a lot of development at this point, constantly get the same repetitive profiles, which are clearly scammers, even after reporting these profiles, it seems though nothing is being done. Not enough verification, or filtering to prevent this, and even after upgrading, it doesn't seem to be worth the money, most profiles are inactive or just people promoting selling content on other sites. App need a lot more restrictions, and needs to stop promoting inactive accounts.", "I got vip. It's ok and I've met one person that was a nice person but not what I imagined from the profile. Other women I've talked to seem to follow the whole scam attempts that you run into on every dating site. Not many matches so far or people close enough near me but not giving up quite yet. Just wish people were more real and honest. Ran into a few fake profiles, and when I match sometimes they seem to suddenly not be interested, which makes me believe it's an algorithm push.", 'Worst app. Used the app for 3 weeks. Zero success. So many fake profiles. If u happened to connect with any, after few text messages you get a pop up asking u to match to continue chatting. Waste of time', 'This app is glitchy, I have to restart it multiple times while talking to someone. Other than it being buggy and glitchy all the time, its a pretty good app.', "Another app afraid to let you see how few people are in your area or how few are recently active. Anytime a service won't let you confirm it has active local users then it's because they don't. What's worse is these kinds of tactics are exactly why they don't attract enough users. You'll have more activity if you stop putting basic confirmations like this behind a paywall, because that's what stops people from signing up or staying with you.", 'Disappointed difficult to understand the use of the site, lack of response, even with all aspects of interest, it made no difference to make a contact, pointless site, total waste of money, and my time 😕 . Total bs site', "I'm not sure how old this app is. Doesn't have hardly anyone on it. And most of the ppl it shows you profile pics of, havent been for wks or months. I should be getting paid to use this app, honestly.", 'I think this is a scam app because it says its free messaging and as soon as I went on the app I had to buy a membership and it wanted me to rate them straight away but at least I only paid £12 for a 1 month membership & the women who liked me where far away.', 'Just signed up. It got my location wrong and to change gota spend 12$, seems un reasonable for information they got wrong. Atleast let the person put in the location once the first time for free.', 'On the screen where it asks to create a username it doesn\'t let me hit "next" to go to the next screen. I was not able to create an account because of the glitch.', "Filled out profile did some likes or interest in a female quite a few actually. Then it was like what jus happened haven't heard anything for 2 days or 3 can only look at the people ya didn't wanna pick or have common. Interests with .KINDA REALLY SHOCKED .", "They don't fact check if a guy is sending or asking for nudes/$&you won't reciprocate they blackmail you&get you banned so it's too hard to make any connections w/real people&then they send you an email suggesting that yoU're fake&asked for$/scamming people when you did no such thing your messages are dry&you get flagged for sending photos or your pet&asking if they like animals. I have enough toys. I'm so convinced that the creators of these dating apps are phishers/hackers/terrorists. Can't d", "Pretty awful; verification took ages, pictures keep seeming to dissappear from my profile and to be able to do anything worthwhile, you've got to pay a pretty steep amount for what seems like an app no one uses", "Very difficult app even though there isn't much to it. I suggest that if somebody likes you that you should be able to see some of the profile to let you know if you are compatible or not.", 'Wildly disappointing. Instantly had 4 likes! Like as soon as my profile was made. Needs work but could be viably good with some changes.', "Definitely the best hook up app available. Find ppl close by and message for free. Doesn't push upgrading like most other apps. Great app!", 'I literally can\'t respond to the first message I\'ve gotten because the bar to enter text is all the way at the bottom of my phone and gets covered by my phone\'s buttons, so whenever I try to respond to the message, all I\'m doing is hitting the "back" or "home" buttons for my phone. That makes the app unusable.', "A lot of the accounts are classic scambait. The filters are... Speculative. You never know what you're going to get. Arbitrary center point for searches and no indication of cities/towns so if it's '40 miles away' in a 100mi search you could be from 60 to 140 out. Maybe it's a European thing.", "The only issue is distance is a little difficult and a lot of profiles don't have pictures. Also the messaging part needs some work. Hard to see the other person's message if you are typing at the same time. Otherwise a decent app", "SO HERE IS THE WORD, DONT TRY & PURCHASE A PACKAGE OR ANYTHING CAUSE I JUST ATTEMPTED TO & AFTER IT CLEARED, THE UPGRADE STILL HASNT TAKEN EFFECT IN THE APP. SO THIS IS AN ISSUE. I SPOKE TOO SOON On another CONSTRUCTIVE note, the glitches & the profile videos not loading needs to be addressed. Also, yuh should be able to chose a max distance between yuh & yur potential matches. A MAX DISTANCE THAT DOESN'T JUST CHANGE BACK TO IT'S DEFAULT.MAX SETTING AFTER YUH TRY & CHANGE IT.", "Trash app. Doesn't update actual current location unless you pay. Only desirable profiles are fakes selling OF.", 'I got on the app and used it for a week without any action. I went to my profile and although I distinctly remember selecting 6\'0" as my height (my actual height), the app placed my height at 5\'0"! Hilarious, but I\'m sure I missed out on plenty of potential matches because of this glitch! Also, not enough people use the app in Florida', "Best hookup app on the market, still bad. All the hookup apps are atrocious because of the prices. This is no different. Sure, $15 isn't much but for a hookup site that's way too much. Plus, while I have had some matches most are either not going to respond or not follow through with making plans. Whether someone is active or not shouldn't be hidden behind a pay wall since that kinda makes the effort of that account wasted.", "Unable to view profile once you've matched/messaged someone, bit clunky but other passable.", "Says someone likes you but it's not a new like, ie after notification, you swipe yes on all of the new swipes (about 3), not one match", "My experience hasn't been so bad although the matches it has provided have been SEVERELY limited. Usually I try not to rate anything I'm not going to give five stars to, but since it kept INSISTING that I rate it every time I check or write a response or two, it gets what it wanted.", 'Good App, easy to use. Did not get any response/messages. I have deleted my account and uninstalled the App.', "Super frustrating that you guys set my location 3 hours away from me. But I can't fix it without paying premium. Which I won't do without using the app for a few days or weeks. So why isn't there an option to just recheck my location??? Don't reply telling me you sent the info to the team.", "Hardly anyone in my area uses this app. Also doesn't help the app pushes you to rate 5 stars....must be why their ratings are that high.", 'Very Easy To find people to talk too and get along with, Im surprised i get actual responses from people instead of Someone trying to sell me content or want me to subscribe to their onlyfans', "Full of fakes and scammers just like most other dating sites. It's a shame that there isn't one site that filters out the bs.", "Money Grab app. Have to have one membership to search and then upgrade again to message. Rip off. Don't use", 'One of those apps which makes the amateurish mistake of having crucial buttons hidden below your Android home & back buttons on certain phones.', "I fell for it... There's a reason that last-seen button is disabled for free accounts. No one within 60 miles in the last month and I'm 20 miles from two cities. Functionally the app seems fine.", "App is pretty good although people who you match tend to be quite far away. Also it's hard to keep track of conversations without timestamps and read notifications.", "I uploaded a photo. They made me do a verification photo. Claims it's not me. Same face, same shirt. Same me. But I cannot go past that."]

title: Rover - Dog Boarding & Walking
description: Rover is the #1 pet sitting and dog walking app. Get trusted pet care in your neighborhood. The Rover app was created for dog people by The Dog PeopleTM. Through the app, get adorable photo updates, GPS tracking of your dog’s walk, an easy way to message sitters or manage your business, and a secure way to book and pay. With over 100,000 pet sitters and dog walkers in the U.S. and Canada, Rover makes it easy to book pet care you can trust. PEACE OF MIND • 95% of reviewed services receive a perfect 5-star rating. • Every service booked on Rover is backed by The Rover Guarantee and 24/7 support. FAST & EASY • Contact and message sitters and dog walkers, right from the app. Receive messages from sitters when you're on the go. • Hassle-free and secure payments, every time. • Get a map of your dog's walk, pee/poo and food/water alerts, and a personalized note from your sitter or dog walker. FOR PET SITTERS AND DOG WALKERS, TOO • Send photos, videos, and messages to pet owners with just a few taps. • Get paid on the go—it’s simple and secure with the Rover app. • Seamlessly manage your business, even if you're at the dog park. • Enable push notifications to respond faster than ever to booking requests. • Create Rover Cards to seamlessly share information with your clients. IN THE PRESS Rover has appeared in: • The New York Times • The Today Show • The Wall Street Journal • USA Today • ABC News • And many more!
summary: Book neighborhood dog boarding, dog walking, pet sitting, and doggy day care.

comments: ["I just started using it. It's good so far, but please allow owners to delete messages when not booking with someone. The messages just build up, and I have to sift through to find one I need. Also, having people outside of my address that I need someone to come to is a little deceptive. Other than those issues so far, it's good. I hope those 2 issues can be resolved. ***Even though nothing is booked and it will move to archive I still think the option to delete would be nice to clean things up", "Great app, we have had a fantastic experience. The app was easy to set up, including the option of making pet profiles for your animals. We found an AMAZING dog walker in our neighborhood, who also doubled as a trainer and border! Love the app, now we have reoccurring walks set up with pre-approved payments, and it couldn't be easier!", "GPS function is still very sketchy and maps are completely inaccurate. They don't show the correct location where I've walked which gives the owner false impression and makes me look bad. Walkers need to be allowed more editing capabilities for their own bookings. Every day should be able to edit individually. I shouldn't have to contact Rover every time I need to tweak some minor detail. When I'm forced to pay such a high fee to use a simple service I expect that it should function at 100%.", "I have been on Rover for about 4 months now. I have noticed a lot of glitches. Sometimes when I hit start walk it doesn't actually start (walk doesn't get recorded), or when I go to add pictures it crashes and I am unable to hit stop to finish without adding the photo...it can be quite frustrating and the timer and gsp are still running until the photo has been added. It also doesn't let you stop more than one walk at a time when walking several dogs at once and so on...", "I haven't started using the app yet but I can't imagine a worse experience. I downloaded the app 30 mins ago and it crashed on me 7-8 times. As I tried to set up a profile for my dog, the description box would freeze up. Each character takes at least 30 seconds to appear after typing. I had to quit and relaunch so many times. I've been writing the same description paragraph, half a sentence at a time, for the last 30 mins!!", 'Easy and straightforward to use, but... Would be nice if you could message a sitter without having to propose a time! Sometimes I just want to chat with a person and set up a meet and greet before I know when I need them. It also sucks that photos that are taken are automatically published publicly. There should be an option to turn that off. It would also be nice if it could automatically usync up with Google Calendar!', "Love the app and the service but there must have been a recent update to the app which makes the calender very hard to use. I can't remember how it used to be but it was much easier Now you have to click each day separately and then edit my capacity to see if you are free. Then back out of that day and repeat for each day. Very cumbersome. Would be nice if you could see your availability for each service and swipe through the days instead of backing out. I often back right out of the app", 'The Rover app is very frustrating. - It continuously sends notifications (to both the walker AND the client!) that a "visit is in progress" both before and after any event. - It doesn\'t stop the clock after a walk until your pictures have uploaded (using up your data!) - It doesn\'t allow you to differentiate the distance you\'re willing to travel or the size of dog you\'re willing to work with, based on the service provided. - And taking 20% of our salary is way too much!!', "I was a sitter through this app! The interface was good. I wish notifications were more customizable. I met many great clients, one of whom I became friends with. I did this for 2 years - until an incident happened with one owner that I admit, I could've handled better. I have not once in the past made a mistake. Rover didn't back me up at all despite my cooperation. All they did was take information, close my account, and didn't give me a chance to try again. Not even probation. Sitters beware.", "This is the most finicky app I have ever used. Sometimes the app works smoothly and things go the way they should. Most other times after many attempts I'm able to request a booking. Then I get a link back telling me to hurry and confirm the booking. I push the link and get taken to some random screen, usually a different one each time. Last night I tried 10 times to confirm booking. They already have my debit card on file so it should have been easy to take my money and confirm the booking.", "I use this app as a dog walker, it has generally been a good experience, except I keep having technical issues with the rover card. One day the map didn't log where I went, so it looked like I had simply gone around the block. And then next walk I went to submit my card, and all looked normal, but then 5 hours later I realized everything I had put into that card hadn't saved, and the map was still going. Therefore it logged my entire trip home. Just feels a bit awkward and clumsy.", "The app it's self is very glitchy. Either not working and shutting down or lagging and making the whole system unusable for several minutes. Customer service is hard to reach out to and get responses from. Though the system is set up to send out quick messages to remind users of its terms of service at any suspect of work being done around the app, they are very slow to respond to concerns brought up through customer service and is difficult to access. All while rising the price", 'The app should display the actual price when searching for sitters instead of the never accurate "starting at" price. I understand the price is based on different criteria but many of them are known ahead of time, for example the number of cats to be watched. This should be accounted for when showing prices. Instead I\'m forced to go into each profile and manually calculate what the price will be.', "Bad app, need much more filters, spent hours trying to find someone. Reached out to three people who said they weren't available even though their calendars fully open. Second, we have a dog who absolutely cannot be around other dogs. You need to have a filter for sitters with and without animals. So that I can eliminate 95% of everyone on the app in order to find those who are actually able to help. Also you can't sort by prices for multiple dogs and an entire stay. Useless", "Great dog walkers, horrible app. There are no filters. People whom are no longer working on the app are still suggested. People you'd like to book again but do not have confirmed availability are suggested. Some require up to three days in advance, though you've indicated that you want to book for the next day, they are suggested to you. Really frustrating and clunky UI. You have to comb through the suggestions for your exact criteria. It shouldn't be so labor intensive to find a walker.", 'I love this app and it is a blessing for me to have a job as a sitter/walker with this app ! I love meeting clients and caring for their pets. But a LOT of technical issues with this app and it is not the easiest to use . They need to show the list of clients pets on the calendar , not just #s of book. Cancelling a booking needs to be more user friendly . It needs to have an Unwalk options if sitter accidentally started a walk timer under the wrong name. And schedule change needs to be simple', "I find this service leaves a lot be desired. Very difficult to resolve issues or even contact customer service directly with any issues. Unless, you don't mind waiting for email responses or being directed to unhelpful automated links that don't resolve the problems. Very expensive and a lot of unreliable walkers and with no accountability for their terrible service. There are some great walkers but few and far between. No weekly or monthly rates.", "I'm a sitter and I signed up using my Facebook account. When I sign in online it works fine, but when I try to sign in with Facebook on the app it completely freezes. There's no new update, I've waited, I've reinstalled, cleared cache and data, I've done everything I can think of. It doesn't work. I don't want to create a new account after going through the whole application process and already submitting for a background check. So basically, the app is unusable for me", "App needs work: trying to add my cat, and where it asks for adoption date, you can't enter a date. You have to scroll back from the current date. Not only that, but I can't even scroll far enough back to my cat's adoption date. I can get the month, but according to Rover, my cat has been alive too long, and they have greyed out the dates. I am also not alone in thinking the pricing structure is very confusing.", "I am very fortunate to have found an amazing sitter. However, the app needs work. The fees can be a bit outrageous for how poorly the app works. Messages always come jumbled up, and it can crash randomly. Sometimes, I don't get notifications either.", "Took me a bit to get used to because it's different from other apps I use, but it's very convenient and everything is handled smoothly in app. You get alerts when services stop and end, and summaries with pictures.", "It would be nice to get some extended features from the website implemented, i.e. bookmarks, but also better search filters and sorting. I understand Rover doesn't want to favor certain sitters but people do have preferences you cannot take away. Not being able to narrow down the search even further, only makes the process of finding a suitable sitter more tedious. Also, please give the user the ability to cancel requests, I hate looking at aged, pending inquiries to irresponsible sitters.", "Rover makes it extremely easy to find very good pet care services for reasonable prices. While there are pieces of the experience that could improve, like the ability to modify a booking while it's happening or the initial account setup, the overall experience is far superior to going into public listings and ads.", "As a sitter, I've had a mostly positive experience but with some room for improvement on the app. As a pet owner/customer, there is definitely more to be desired. I've sent my suggestions for improvements on both fronts, and their team acknowledged all of the suggestions right away but I have yet to see any implemented.", 'Easy to book. Frustratingly hard to cancel. My dog has issues. booked a sitter and meet up before to make sure it was OK. Both agreed it would not be a good match. I cancelled on Rover. "Rover needs to review this request before we cancel and refund." 6 days later, no response. No option to see status in my dashboard. No live chat to ask. No phone number listed. Googled phone number for human and called. Bad automated responses and a transfer before I got it cancelled.', "At first I liked this app but it became intermittent, it didn't pass on every message to everyone. But the biggest problem: each time we make an appointment, it charges us $3 and our puppy care provider $5!!! Way way too much money for the service. We simply moved to a group text.", 'Overall, very good app. And very helpful people able to look after your pets. The app has a few quirks that could do with making it a little clearer, but other than that, seems good.', "the numbers you supply your employees to text from, I am unable to reply to. my sitters were not getting my texts, and they were looking at me as the faulty communicator. i don't like that. once i figured out that your texting system works one way, I just have had to open up the app each time. it's annoying, but necessary. everything else has been satisfactory.", "Already not liking the fact that I can't log on from my Google account to the app...it tells me to leave, then open a web browser 1st....JUST TO ACCESS THE APP?? ...Thumbs down Rover! Most apps let you create and log in from the app...who wants to go open an https browser if I've downloaded your app to do all of this?? Bad design Rover.", "Great site, easy to use. I think my only complaint is that the fees were hefty to modify a visit and to cancel a day when we were camping and cut short due to weather...both fees applied. Otherwise totally appreciate the service, and appreciate that the changes have to be initiated by the sitter so they don't get screwed over. Good care for my furries!", "Review as a walker - the design of the app is clunky, buggy and quite slow. The sorting/searching of the messaging system is reminiscent of a Moodle forum from 2005. They will spam your email with irrelevant suggestions. The degree of support walkers get is not much at all. As a walker you are quite vulnerable to damage and injury without financial support or recompense from the company. It's useful as a side Hussle... But quite liable to use as a main source of income.", "The Rover app and whole experience is good. I have used it many times for dog sitting and it's been great. However it's becoming just too expensive and I will now only use Rover as a last resort. The latest occasion ended up being £65 for a 1 night stay. That was for someone whose initial advertised rate was £24/night. Too much I'm afraid.", "App is difficult to navigate - it's hard to see your schedule for upcoming walks, as well as invoices and charges. Customer service is non-responsive. They charge both caregivers and owners a fee, yet they don't provide any support whatsoever. I do NOT recommend using this app or the service in general.", "I've been a sitter on the app since 2018 and I am changing my review for a 4TH TIME! AS A SITTER I DO NOT THINK THESE RECENT UPDATES ARE HELPFUL!STOP! The rating service needs to change, go back to private, and be available for sitters to view from the phone app. The calendar immediately needs to STOPbeing updated! After this most recent update where you can now view individual days, if you click on it takes you to a blank screen and two circles which I assume are the bookings but don't show up.", "Finding people on the app that have their timetable up to date is so difficult, people's pricing in search differes from what they have on their profile and best of all there is a 25% service charge per booking to boot! That means £6.25 service charge for a booking of £25....that is after you put in the effort of actually finding a person that has accurate information on or that doesn't mess you around. Do not recommend.", "The app itself is terrible to manage. Doesn't do a good job at telling you what is/isn't booked and what's pending or not pending. If you have a weekly set up, like we do, and need to cancel 1 of the days, you must contact the host and have them cancel for you. Even if you're canceling a Thursday appointment and it's Tuesday. Because the week already started. Which doesn't make sense as to why I need to reach out to the host. Customer service is nonexistent. Looking into daycare away from Rover.", "It's very frustrating that the only way you can contact support for a non emergency is through email. I need to make a modification the day of, and instead of the owner the request went to support. They have not approved the request, nor are they responding to my emails. It would be really helpful if there was a number that could be called to handle this situation, or respond to emails more timely.", "So you'll pay for your membership and then they will take 20% and up everytime you book someone. Then if you take a job and the person pays you cash then rover will deactivate your account and not let you ever get it back. Idk if I would recommend this app. I found one for completely free and they don't take any of your money and it offers more than just animal jobs. Rover support isn't very helpful either.", 'Great easy to use app. I appreciate that you have multiple options for both dogs and cats to either get daily walks, drop-in visits, in-home care, and even housesitting. Our cat is way less stressed being able to stay at home than having to go to the border while we are away.', 'CORRECT THE BOOKING TIMES PROBLEM:: The booking \'time-frame\' has confused every owner that has contacted me. The requirement to select 4 different times doesn\'t work (especially since you only calculate the time from END start to END end). Please remove the "extra" time boxes, which also throw off the calculated care rates!!']

We’ll guide you through the process in three easy steps: STEP 1: TELL US ABOUT YOURSELF Your canadian dating journey on our dating app starts with the Compatibility Quiz. STEP 2: LEARN MORE ABOUT YOUR PERSONALITY Your answers to the Compatibility Quiz are compiled to create a Personality Profile, an informative report about your character, lifestyle, relationship behavior and communication style. The results allow eharmony to do the work for you and match you with compatible singles. STEP 3: MATCH WITH CANADIAN COMPATIBLE SINGLES It’s finally time to start dating. Through your Match List you’ll have access to each of your match’s profiles so you can better understand who they are as a person. The list is constantly updated as new members join so you’ll never miss an opportunity to fall in love. WHAT HAPPENS NEXT? It’s time to connect with your matches and meet new people! Try one of our different communication features: Send a smile, start a conversation with an icebreaker or use our similarities cards to explore interesting and character traits you and your match share. eharmony is the #1 Trusted Dating App. We have a skilled in-house Trust and Safety team to ensure our platform is safe, inclusive, and welcoming to every member of our community. This gives you full access to all of eharmony’s functions and capabilities, making it much easier to find a connect with your ideal partner. Membership structure – Online dating is a journey and shouldn’t be rushed. We believe that shorter plans don’t give you the time to properly get to know your matches, which is why we offer our Premium Membership in 6, 12, or 24-month plans. comments: ["Can't even contact someone via app, click on help and options and nothing. Cheap. Very few people to match with and often not even close to preferences. Biggest peeve is no photos! No verification process. You should make it mandatory to include a photo and verify it. I have dozens of matches of 'quotes' but I'm not looking to date a quote! I want to see verified visual as physical appearance is important (not Hollywood model but takes care of themselves, and a real person vs scam). Bad app", "Terrible. The matches were horrific(like cartoon villain bad), many with no photos, many without subscription, so they couldn't chat even if I wanted to, many that hadn't been online for weeks. I asked for a refund in less than 24 hours of subscription, and they gave me the song and dance about the £65 personalized report; which was the multiple choice questionnaire that everyone fills out and it generates an algorithm. And it matched me with Humpty Dumpty. Not worth £65. That's for sure.", 'The site is great. the app sucks. when I message someone back the app will delete my message part way through or as most of the time it just won\'t send the message at all. If I click on "contact us" in settings you get zilch. Same as "feedback". I called eharmony and they said there was a problem with the app and delete and reinstall it. I tried that, it worked a few times but now back to the same issues. It\'s very frustrating as this is one most expensive sites there is. I would not recommend.', "Has potential, but the user's base is horrible. Design and feature-wise the app is okay. The problem I'm experiencing is that the match quality is very bad. Most users have only one photo, with no effort given to profiles, I'd say about a third of profiles shown to me have no photos at all. Of the select few profiles that were appealing, none of them responded; which I assume means they are free users. Waste of money.", 'It\'s a good app, a bit of a pioneer but it\'s gotten rather expensive and while it is more "high tech"with better matching criteria than other dating sites, it has very few subscribers. If there was more free features, like being able to see the photos of your matches, it might be more widely used. But to spend the high monthly subscription blindly makes it a hard decision. Used to be great, but now there\'s competition, times are changing.', 'Absolutely the worst dating app ever. They offer no trial period, and as soon as you sign up, they lock you into a contract, relying on the fact that you wont read through pages of nonsense and figure out that cancelation of services does not mean cancelation of payment. Once you are locked in, they provide you with 10 matches, that look like they just came out of prison, and expect you to just continue paying for the no service they provide. And if you contact them, they say," oh too bad. "', 'Sent a request to cancel my subscription early and, at this time removed the automatic renewal. However, I never heard anything back about my cancelation (figured it had been declined). Jump forward, and now they are charging me for a whole year subscription and will not process a refund. The system keeps no log of changes for the user to view, so all my requests and changes do not appear presently. I know I did these changes as I even thought about taking screenshots. SCAMMERS!!!', "Not worth it. The subscription is actually a contract. There is no getting out of it. And no one is even in my area EVER so I am paying for absolutely NOTHING. I'm not able to match with anyone. So I feel completely screwed over... the only part that was enjoyable was the long psychological test at the beginning. Then you can't see messages unless your subscribe. So you don't get to actually try it and know if you like it before committing to high payments that you cannot back out of. Shameful.", "ZERO stars, waste of time. DO NOT buy the membership. Read all the 1 star reviews, all 100% correct. I was duped by the fancy commercials, fancy question. Poor filters, very bad UI for an app you pay so much for. I was suckered into buying the 1 year, can't get even a portion of my money back, canceling the auto renew was difficult and hidden. Matches are horrible, I've been on several dating app, this has got to be the most expensive and the absolutely WORST!!! DO NOT WASTE YOUR MONEY AND TIME.", "App works from a basic standpoint but the interface is clunky and messages appear to sometimes take a second attempt to send. There seems to be a repeated delay in doing anything which is frustrating. This is not device based as I've tried it on a mid tier phone to a flagship device. It's the not the hardware. Nonetheless, it serves its basic functions: see your matches, communicate and access your account settings. Wish it was just optimized.", "I read a lot of reviews and thought I'd try anyway. I read their terms re: renewal so I could cancel if I needed. I read there is a reminder notification (via email, I believe) about renewal and you can decide at that point if you want to renew or cancel. I waited...nothing but an email thanking me for using the app, and a $430 charge to my credit card. Thats a lot of money for the lack of success the app brought. I'm waiting for customer service to get back to me... UPDATE...no refund.", "Premium NOT worth the $. Payed way more than expected. 1yr membership ended up being 400$ (-50$promo). Tried to cancel after 7 months. Charged initial setup and 2 quarterly payments. Do not want to continue, but they won't cancel my premium membership until after a yr and have told me they will be charging me the last quarterly payment(95$). DO NOT pay for long term memberships (even though its cheaper/month). You will be stuck paying the full term. The app itself is ok, but not worth the $", 'Absolutely pointless app. as far as I can figure both people have to pay in order to send actual messages to one another may be mistaken but their customer support has failed to answer this question at all despite multiple message. so as far as I can figure you could pay for your membership and still not be able to message people. waste of money and a waste of time', "Buyer Beware - (This review is my opinion): There is a reason there ISN'T a 24 hour trial version. In fact be very careful if you do pay, I got suckered into a 12 month subscription. If you do decide to try, I'd suggest one month only. Watch out though, because they will 'auto' renew your subscription which means you could be in for a very unpleasant surprise at the end of your term when they ding your credit card for a renewal term. No refunds and customer service with a live person was non-existent. I signed up, but immediately after felt that I needed more time so wanted to cancel and sign up later. They don't have a cooling off period (unless you are lucky to live in a couple states that protect you). Once they have your money, they have an iron clad legal agreement. No backing out, so if you want to try, I'd urge you to pay only for 30 days and make sure to disable the sneaky default 'auto' renew. Bad business practices in my opinion and for that reason will never pay for this service again. Horrible. Telling anyone who is dating to stay away. Taking my money elsewhere, oh wait, can't they took it. Now that I'm ready for dating, much prefer Bumble! Good luck.", 'A year ago I purchased a membership and let me tell you it was the biggest mistake I made. I got one match from the pricey subscription they have. I think I paid like $60 for a month or something. This app cant get more pay to use than it is. They have no accessible features unless you pay. And I hate these kinds of apps so much because they have so many false ads. They make theirself look so good on their TV ads but its worse than they say.', "Absolutely ridiculous experience. Locked in for a year without the ability to cancel or refund. Should have done more research on this before signing up, but honestly, there's not much online about this service in Canada, I didn't notice that the trials or refund policy are all for other countries, Canada has no grace period whatsoever. Also, there are not many matches in my area, a lot of profiles are without picture or even a name! Ugh, so angry at myself for getting into this mess!", "It will have you go through a lengthy sign up, just to find out you can barely do anything without paying. You can't even view other members photos for free. And, you can't get a payed membership through the app. You have to go to the website. And, uploaded photos could take hours to actually appear on your profile cause they want to review them, so it's pointless to try to match with anyone immediately since it'll just be a blank profile for a while. Horrible service.", "Do NOT bother subscribing to this! It won't let you see the pictures unless you pay. I paid and there isn't much. There are just as many catfish here as on any other site and a lot less variety. When I went to cancel, it gave me the option of going monthly. I chose it, but somehow it still said i was still at 6 months and when I went to contact customer service, they basically said too bad. I even received an email that says they dont offer month-to-month lol! Don't waste your time or money!", 'The service might be worthwhile. The app sucks. Specifically, in trying to purchase a membership with their advertise 60% off.... their link within the app is "wonky" ( That\'s a technical term, I was a programmer and worked in networking for many years). The link actually lets me go nowhere. I could go to the website and purchase the service, But really, if they aren\'t even going to check their work before they put the app out I wouldn\'t trust them with any method of payment. Uninstall it!!', "It's been just an okay experience for me. I'm very pleased with the low number of catfishers and scammers I have encountered since joining. Only one, really. And his profile was deleted rather quickly. Kudos there!! It is bothersome, however, that you can't filter out guys who have no photo on their profile, which is a huge number for me, anyway.", "The premium upgrade was incredibly misleading. I realized the day I upgraded that it took more out of my bank account than what I realized. I canceled the service the same day I upgraded. I keep trying to reach customer service for a refund, but the customer service chat system keeps loading a blank page. I emailed them, and I still have not gotten a response even though they have a 3 day refund policy. I can't find a phone number online.", "Easily the most expensive dating app out there. And if you use it for free, you can't so much as send a message to another user. Even if someone likes you with a premium account and send you a message you still can't see it. Blatantly money grabbing, this app asks for way too much to just get the baseline features other apps would give you for free. I wish I could give less stars. $400 for 6 months? In this economy? And that's the cheapest option.", "No point in using. Yes it's good but why would I want to swipe right on someone if I can't even see what they look like? In order to view photos you have to become a premium member. Why would I pay for premium just to see a photo of someone when I can go to another dating app that does everything this one does including allow you to see pictures but for free.", "SCAM!! I downloaded this 14/08. You can't see images unless you pay for subscription, paid for it. Your pics take 24 hours to validate. I cancelled within hours of paying for premium not great app not many potential matches either (same day). They charged me £65 (apparently half price) of some report that I did not request nor knew I even had.", "Eharmony is a total SCAM. Stay AWAY! After spending an hour setting up the account, you can't see any photos on the free basic account. I paid for the premium version. After a couple of days, I wanted to cancel my subscription and delete my account. Eharmony made it impossible to do so, after numerous emails back and forth, they finally agreed to delete my account but have advised me that I am required to continue to pay for the next 12 months!! Absolute SCAM.", "Absolute waste of money. Signed up and only had 6 matches within 30 miles, which increased to about 15 within 60 miles. They also used my answers to he personality questionnaire from over 2 years ago. Ridiculous considering they make it clear in the T&Cs that you can't get a refund on this element. Your time would be better spent on the other free dating apps in the market.", 'GIGANTIC WASTE OF MONEY. They clearly know they have an inferior product, because they lock you into a 6 month contract to be able to function at all in the app. Don\'t bother, learn from my mistakes. The filters are garbage, there are no worthwhile functions the free apps don\'t have, and the "personality quiz" is a farce. If I could delete the app without losing more money, I absolutely would.', 'My photos were declined for having multiple people in them, even though I was the only one in the photo. My bio was declined for violating community standards, even though there was absolutely nothing inappropriate in my bio. The problem here is that the algorithms and/or people reviewing things have the combined IQ of a carrot. Oh, and it is by far the most expensive dating app on the market. Enjoy!', "No way to skip or view anyone. You spend a half hour answering all these questions and making a profile just to find out you can't do anything without a subscription. You can't see anyone's picture without subscribing. I'm very disappointed with how much time it took just to be disappointed when you're done. Absolutely horrible app. I don't recommend it at all.", "Bait and switch at its finest. The concept and match profiles are good. When it comes to messaging someone, after two messages you can't read each other's message unless you pay. Everyone's images are blurred out as well unless you pay. Clever scheme guys, I'm not falling for it. Neither should you.", "Super expensive for premium benefits that aren't even worth it. I thought I canceled but for some reason they never stopped expecting monthly payment. In the end they threatened to report me to debt collectors if I didn't pay $240 up front. I paid the money but I'm still pissed. I also think it's ridiculous that you are paying to see people's faces and to send messages. That's it. The only thing that's sort of worth the money is having better selection to fit your wants.", "Recommended the app by a friend who used it years ago. Eharmony forces you into a 6mo multi-payment thing to sign up and view matches. My matches have been *terrible*, so i cancelled, but its still billing me. By far the worst of the dating apps for matches, worst for shadey payment practices, and worst for usability. I've had way better success on bumble and hinge. I hope eharmony goes bankrupt for their scam-focused behaviors.", 'The app is mostly stable. The match rating is interesting to say the least, however it is only somewhat accurate. Personalitys may match with lesser ratings. Message and being specific helps.', "It's really been a disappointing experience. I was hoping it would have been different but it's just as full of shallow people as any other dating site/app. Don't sign up with them, you won't get your money back and your stuck with it until your subscription ends. So you have to pay to be reminded how hopeless your situation is.", "There's a reason they make you sign up for 6 months. It's the WORST dating site out there. I went through all the matches in ALL of Ontario within the first few days. I signed up for a monthly payment thinking I could cancel, but they told me they would not cancel it. Now I'm stuck with these monthly payments for another 5 months for basically nothing. Don't make the same mistake I made! Stay well away from this app!!", "Very poor app. I will recommend not to sign up for membership because it is for the whole term you chose. You can cancel a any time but you will be charged for the remaining balance. It only has an algorithm for personality which I'm not sure how many people pay attention to that. However, you can't sort your matches according with their rating. Honestly speaking, don't waste your money here.", 'Very few matches and tons of profiles with no pictures. Plus the questionnaire that is supposed to help you match with similar people is worthless. EXTREMELY expensive for what you get (over $400 for 6 months...thought I was signing up for $80)', "What a joke, I have not even been on the site a month and wanted to cancel. They stop the renewal but still have to pay for the year. It's the same pictures that come up every time even after you had had clicked no to the person. Eharmony is a joke and a rip off. They are trying to help you find a relationship they are just trying to rip ppl off that are looking for one. The ad is a joke and so is the site. Worst dating site I have ever tried out.", 'Too expensive! Not worth the cost. The "science" counts for little when half my matches didn\'t include pictures. Read your terms & conditions carefully. They will auto renew and upcharge you. I\'ve had better results using free competitors. Too limited on subscription options. 6 months is the shortest option. Seems odd that a dating app would only offer long term subscription options. If the app works as intended than you wouldn\'t need to have a year long subscription. So disappointed.', "After a few weeks in, on having my paid subscription, I've been having glitches app glitches where I message matches, and they don't appear in my matches tab. There's no in-app support, and the 3 emails I sent haven't been responded to in a few days now... I'll update this post if/when this issue gets resolved."]
